Date: Mon 10 Jul 2000
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Interfax-Kazakhstan Sun 09 Jul 2000 0922 GMT in Russian [edited

Four in hospital with suspected anthrax in Kazakh southern town
---------------------------------------------------------------
Four people with a preliminary diagnosis of anthrax were admitted to the
hospital for infectious diseases in Shymkent (administrative centre of
South Kazakhstan Region) yesterday, [according to the republican Agency
for Emergency Situations. The cause of the disease and people with whom
[the patients were in contact are being established, the agency said.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[In personal discussions earlier this year with the Kazakh public health
officials in Almaty they commented on the increasing annual incidence in
humans, which clearly indicates ongoing problems with the veterinary
control and identification of this livestock disease. - Mod. MHJ
